PARIS, France, December 8 – South Africa were drawn alongside Germany, Spain and China in Group B for the Women’s World Cup to be held in France next year. The draw was held on Saturday in Paris. The tournament will take place from June 7 to July 7 in 2019. Nigeria were drawn in Group A with Norway, South Korea and hosts France. In Group E, Cameroon were drawn alongside New Zealand, Canada and the Netherlands. World Cup groups: Group A: France, South Korea, Norway, Nigeria Group B: Germany, China, Spain, South Africa Group C: Australia, Italy, Brazil, Jamaica Group E: Canada, Cameroon, New Zealand, Netherlands Group F: USA, Thailand, Chile, Sweden